<div class="bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-100">
  <.marketing_nav current={:docs} />

  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400">Compare</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 md:text-5xl">
        Slack ops bots vs emisar
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-zinc-400">
        Chat is useful for coordination. It is a weak execution boundary once AI agents
        start invoking production operations.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-50">
        The channel is not the control plane
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
        Slash commands and bot messages make operations accessible, but permission checks,
        approvals, output retention, and ownership tend to remain fragmented across handlers
        and channel conventions. emisar keeps the chat or LLM client at the request layer and
        moves enforcement into a dedicated control plane and on-host runner.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-50">Side-by-side</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-zinc-900">
        <table class="min-w-[680px] text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-zinc-950/80 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-500">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Concern</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Slack ops bot</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">emisar</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-900 text-zinc-300">
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Caller interface</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Slash commands and message parsing</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Typed MCP tools with declared schemas</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Authorization</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Channel membership and custom checks</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Roles, per-user runner scopes, policy gates</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Approval</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Reaction or message convention</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Contextual approve/deny with revocable standing grants</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Output</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Channel messages and thread history</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Live run output with redaction and terminal state</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Action drift</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Depends on bot deployment process</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Changed pack hashes block dispatch pending review</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Audit export</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Chat export plus application logs</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">
                Tamper-evident host journal (<code>emisar audit verify</code>), searchable cloud
                audit, read-only SIEM token
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-50">Keep Slack in the workflow</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
        emisar does not need to replace team communication. Operators can still coordinate in
        Slack while the action contract, policy decision, approval, run state, and audit record
        live in the product built to own them. A disciplined bot with real RBAC and interactive
        approvals narrows the gap — emisar's point is that you get that boundary by default,
        on-host, across every MCP client, not bolted onto one channel.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-x-6 gap-y-3 border-t border-zinc-900 pt-8 text-sm">
        <.link
          navigate={~p"/docs/connect-an-llm"}
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
        >
          Connect an LLM <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
        </.link>
        <.link
          navigate={~p"/docs/security-model"}
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
        >
          Policy &amp; approvals <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
        </.link>
        <.link
          navigate={~p"/packs"}
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
        >
          Pack registry <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
        </.link>
        <.link
          navigate={~p"/pricing"}
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
        >
          Pricing <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
        </.link>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <.marketing_footer />
</div>
